cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the problem of building taxonomies from textual and visual data, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a probabilistic model and uses machine learning techniques to learn the taxonomies, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to evaluate the performance of the model, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another possible sub-category.
